<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880916-0109 </DOCNO><HL> Nova to Buy 50% of Alberta Gas </HL><SO> </SO><CO> T.BNS NVA </CO><IN> LNG TNM </IN><DATELINE> CALGARY, Alberta  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Nova Corp. of Alberta said it agreed to buy 50% of Alberta Gas Chemicals Ltd. from Bank of Nova Scotia for 40 million Canadian dollars (U.S.$32.7 million). Nova, which already owned the other 50% of Alberta Gas Chemicals, said the new unit will be integrated with its Novacor Chemicals Ltd. unit.    Nova is a natural-gas transportation and petrochemical company. Edmonton, Alberta-based Alberta Gas Chemicals is Canada's largest methanol producer. </TEXT></DOC>